Description:
   Dissolution Protocol is the Cipher's advanced survival technique. When
   activated, the operative executes a controlled collapse, appearing to all
   observers as if they have been killed or incapacitated. The Cipher enters
   a state of feigned death, removing themselves from combat entirely until
   they choose to reengage.

   While in this state the Cipher is ignored by enemies and ticks no combat
   timers. The protocol is a calculated strategic withdrawal rather than an
   actual retreat — the operative uses the brief window to assess the
   situation, recover slightly, and choose the optimal moment to reveal
   their continued presence. Enemies must be successfully deceived for the
   protocol to take effect; highly aware opponents may see through the ruse.
*******************************************************************************
